00:17:10.369 --> 00:17:11.599
going in.

00:17:11.599 --> 00:17:14.450
And T3, we'll call Tout.

00:17:14.450 --> 00:17:20.960
So let's rewrite the
Q equation, the Q-eq,

00:17:20.960 --> 00:17:22.819
with these symbols in there.

00:17:22.819 --> 00:17:24.829
And the last thing
to note, what's

00:17:24.829 --> 00:17:28.650
Q for elastic scattering?

00:17:28.650 --> 00:17:30.220
0, yes.

00:17:30.220 --> 00:17:32.750
Because no mass is turned
into energy or vice versa.

00:17:32.750 --> 00:17:37.180
So to rewrite the whole
Q equation, we'll get 0

00:17:37.180 --> 00:17:45.520
equals Tin times M1 over
M4, which is just 1 over A,

00:17:45.520 --> 00:17:55.600
minus 1 plus Tout times
1 plus M3 over M4.

00:17:55.600 --> 00:18:04.670
M3 is also 1, M4 is also
A. And minus 2 root M1 M3.

00:18:04.670 --> 00:18:07.160
They're both 1.

00:18:07.160 --> 00:18:13.690
Tin Tout cosine theta.

00:18:13.690 --> 00:18:15.570
So this looks a
whole lot simpler.

00:18:15.570 --> 00:18:18.480
I'm going to do one quick
thing right here and take

00:18:18.480 --> 00:18:22.440
the minus sign that's hiding
in here outside this equation.

00:18:22.440 --> 00:18:26.417
It's going to make the
form a lot simpler.

00:18:26.417 --> 00:18:28.500
So I'm just multiplying
the inside and the outside

00:18:28.500 --> 00:18:30.375
of this term by negative
1, but hopefully you

00:18:30.375 --> 00:18:31.920
can see that it's
the same thing.

00:18:31.920 --> 00:18:34.250
It will just make the form
a lot nicer in the end.

00:18:34.250 --> 00:18:35.850
And so now we want
to start asking,

00:18:35.850 --> 00:18:39.120
what is the maximum
and minimum energy

00:18:39.120 --> 00:18:41.895
that the neutron can lose?

00:18:41.895 --> 00:18:43.270
So let's start
with the easy one.

00:18:43.270 --> 00:18:45.118
What is the minimum
amount of energy

00:18:45.118 --> 00:18:46.285
