AUDIENCE: 0.

00:18:53.260 --> 00:18:54.290
MICHAEL SHORT: 0.

00:18:54.290 --> 00:18:57.490
And if the neutron comes in--

00:18:57.490 --> 00:19:02.350
if theta equals
0, then you end up

00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:08.230
with actually Tin
will equal Tout.

00:19:08.230 --> 00:19:13.720
And, that way, let's say
delta T1 or delta T neutron

00:19:13.720 --> 00:19:14.920
could equal 0.

00:19:14.920 --> 00:19:19.420
So a neutron can lose at
