00:19:24.530 --> 00:19:27.950
Now let's take the other case.

00:19:27.950 --> 00:19:30.680
At what angle would
you think the neutron

00:19:30.680 --> 00:19:36.590
would transfer as much energy as
possible to the recoil nucleus?

00:19:36.590 --> 00:19:39.360
So if we have a big
nucleus of mass A

00:19:39.360 --> 00:19:46.230
and we have a little neutron
firing at it, at which angle

00:19:46.230 --> 00:19:47.850
does it transfer
the most energy?

00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:52.230
Yes.

00:19:52.230 --> 00:19:52.930
AUDIENCE: Pi?

00:19:52.930 --> 00:19:53.812
If it's like--

00:19:53.812 --> 00:19:54.770
MICHAEL SHORT: Exactly.

00:19:54.770 --> 00:19:56.610
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:19:56.610 --> 00:19:59.960
MICHAEL SHORT: At theta
